    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I am having a similar issue with InstantSearchNext (\"react-instantsearch-nextjs\": \"0.3.17\"),  (▲ Next.js 14.2.4)\r\n\r\n\"Can't perform a React state update on a component that hasn't mounted yet. This indicates that you have a side-effect in your render function that asynchronously later calls tries to update the component.\"\r\n\r\nI am not 100% sure what is causing the error. Replacing `InstantSearchNext` with `InstantSearch`-Component seems to resolve the issue. @Haroenv Could this be related? Or should I create a new issue?",
